KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS:
- ctrl + shift + N = new window/new instance of vscode
- shift + alt + enter = insert new line above.
- ctrl + enter = insert new line below.
- ctrl + shift + alt + ' = copy line up. 
- ctrl + shift + alt + / = copy line down.  
- ctrl + shift + k = delete the line.
- ctrl + up/down = scroll.
- alt + up/down = move line up and down.
- alt + click = multiple cursor.
- ctlr + shift + [/] = toggle between open and fold.
- ctrl + -/= = zoom in/out.
- ctrl + ` = toggle terminal.
- alt + enter = put cursor at the end of every "ctrl + f" word.
// OR
- ctrl + shift + l = multiple cursor over the word where the cursor is.
- ctrl + b = toggle sidebar explorer.
- click ------to-----> shift + click = selects the region
- ctrl + k ctrl + 0 = fold all
- ctrl + k ctrl + j = unfold all
- ctrl + l = higlight/select a line completely
--------------------------------------------
- ctrl + j ctrl + s -> settings.json
- ctrl + k ctrl + s -> keyboard settings
- ctrl + shift + right/left -> word selection
